This paper is about learning-to-rank algorithms, which are commonly used in information retrieval (IR) tasks such as web search and recommendation systems. Therefore, cs.IR is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a deep neural network architecture for learning groupwise scoring functions, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper involves natural language processing (NLP) techniques such as document ranking and relevance ordering, which are relevant to sub-categories such as cs.CL (computational linguistics) and cs.CV (computer vision). Finally, the paper uses state-of-the-art techniques in deep learning and optimization, which are relevant to sub-category cs.AI (artificial intelligence).
